              Strings

A String in Java is an object that represents a sequence of characters.
Defined in the java.lang package.
Java Strings are immutable (once created, cannot be changed).

String str1 = "Hello";               // String literal
String str2 = new String("World");   // Using constructor

 String pool
String a = "Java";
String b = "Java";
System.out.println(a == b); // true

| Method                  | Description                           |
| ----------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `length()`              | Returns the length of the string      |
| `charAt(index)`         | Returns character at a specific index |
| `substring(start, end)` | Extracts substring                    |
| `toLowerCase()`         | Converts to lowercase                 |
| `toUpperCase()`         | Converts to uppercase                 |
| `trim()`                | Removes leading and trailing spaces   |
| `equals(str)`           | Compares two strings (case-sensitive) |
| `equalsIgnoreCase(str)` | Case-insensitive comparison           |
| `compareTo(str)`        | Lexicographical comparison            |
| `contains(seq)`         | Checks if sequence exists             |
| `replace(old, new)`     | Replaces character or string          |
| `split(regex)`          | Splits string based on regex          |
